DCI officers have recovered a firearm stolen from a civilian firearm holder. In a tweet on Sunday, DCI said, "A revolver pistol with five rounds of ammunition reported stolen from a civilian fiream holder on 23/6/2019 was today recovered at Kayole area in NaivashaÂ  and three arrests made." Officers acted on a tip off the DCI and first arrested  James Lokol Kamais, 21, from within Naivasha. The first suspect then led to the second suspect in Kihoto area where 31-year-old Joseph Odeko was also arrested. Odeko led the officers to Karagita area, where the third suspect, Ibrahim Mwangi Wanyoike was arrested, leading way to his house in Kayole.